  "name": "Mycoplasma genitalium G37",
  "niche": {
    "entity_count": 120,
    "description": "Curated contaminant-anchor roster \u00d7 CDS GCF_000027325.1 ASM2732v1 (NCBI, public domain). 15 loci: the glycolysis backbone (Mycoplasma's sole ATP route \u2014 it has lost the TCA cycle / cytochromes) + the MgPa cytadherence/adhesin apparatus (the host-grip machinery of the filter-passing parasite). M. genitalium G37: ~580 kb / ~470-485 genes; no cell wall (Mollicutes) -> passes 0.22 um filters, intrinsically beta-lactam-resistant; reaches 10^8/mL non-turbid (cryptic contamination). The immigration kernel reads role + trait levers, not specific genes (ADR-019 S0, Mode A contaminant).",
    "temp_optimum": 0.62,
    "parent_key": null,
    "trophic_role": "heterotroph"
